From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 15:45:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Give DualShock speaker a stable controller name.

DualShock 4 exposes its controller speaker path through Pulse as the render
endpoint "DualShock 4 [CUH-ZCT2x] Analog Stereo".  That physical name is still
the correct backend route, but Spider-Man Remastered does not reliably bind its
controller-effect stream to that endpoint after switching from DualSense /
DualSense Edge to DualShock.

Keep the real Pulse endpoint in MMDevice::drv_id so removal and routing still
match the physical device, but advertise the Windows-facing friendly name as a
controller speaker.  The stale AudioEndpoint cleanup already knows this name,
and the normal DualSense / DualSense Edge naming stays untouched.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index 0825a706ad2..123456789ab 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1412,6 +1412,10 @@ static MMDevice *MMDevice_Create(const WCHAR *name, GUID *id, EDataFlow flow, DW
     free(cur->drv_id);
     cur->drv_id = wcsdup(name);
     device_iname = cur->drv_id;
+    if (dualsense_mono_endpoint &&
+            dualsense_mono_endpoint_model_name(name) == DUALSENSE_MONO_MODEL_DUALSHOCK)
+        device_iname = L"DualShock 4 Wireless Controller Speaker";
+
     swprintf(friendly_name, FRIENDLY_NAME_MAX, friendly_name_fmt, device_desc, device_iname);
     cur->removed = FALSE;
     cur->hide_from_collection = FALSE;
